'''''Howard the Duck''''', also known as '''''Howard the Duck: Adventure on Volcano Island''''',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldofspectrum.org/infoseekid.cgi?id=0002370 |title=Howard the Duck|publisher=WorldofSpectrum.org |access-date=22 July 2015}}</ref> is an action [[video game]] released in 1986 by [[Activision]] for the [[ZX Spectrum]], [[Commodore 64]] and [[Apple II]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mobygames.com/game/howard-the-duck/release-info |title=Howard the Duck: Releases|publisher=[[MobyGames]] |access-date=22 July 2015}}</ref> The game is a [[tie-in]] to the film ''[[Howard the Duck (film)|Howard the Duck]]'' from the same year.

==Gameplay==
The game involves players controlling [[Howard the Duck]] to save his best friends, Phil and [[Beverly Switzler|Beverly]]. After being parachuted to Volcano Island, Howard needs to find a backpack to proceed with the search. The game consists then of four levels, in the last of which Howard, armed with a neutron gun, will finally face Overlord.

==Reception==
Like [[Howard the Duck (film)|the film]], the game also received fairly negative reviews.<ref>{{cite web|title=Howard the Duck: Reviews|url=http://www.mobygames.com/game/howard-the-duck/mobyrank|website=[[MobyGames]]|access-date=27 November 2015}}</ref> ''Computer Gamer'' gave an overall 55%, by stating "beautifully presented, and well-programmed, it rates as one of Activision's better recent releases and deserves consideration outside its [[Howard the Duck (film)|unfortunate tie-in]]", predicting, however, low longevity.<ref>{{cite journal  |date=1987 |title=Howard the Duck |url=https://archive.org/stream/Computer_Gamer_Issue_23_1987-02_Argus_Press_GB#page/n20/mode/1up |journal= Computer Game |issue=23 |pages=21 |access-date=27 July 2015}}</ref> ''[[Aktueller Software Markt]]'' described the game as not fulfilling the expectancies and not worth the money.<ref>{{cite journal |date=1987 |title=Eine Ente geht "baden"|url=https://archive.org/stream/asm_magazine-1987-03/ASM_03_1987#page/n7/mode/2up |journal= Aktueller Software Markt |issue=3 |pages=9 |access-date=27 July 2015}}</ref>

